The paper discusses compressive sensing, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The proposed method involves the use of structured sensing matrices and reconstruction algorithms, which are related to machine learning (cs.LG) and signal processing (cs.SP). The paper also mentions the use of belief propagation algorithms, which are commonly used in distributed systems and networks (cs.DS) as well as in statistical inference (cs.SI).
